description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Resident Clinical Pharmacist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 + Emergency Duty Commitment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£31, 365 – £37,890 + EDC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently have vacancies within our resident clinical pharmacy team and are seeking enthusiastic pharmacists to work with our friendly, supportive and highly trained clinical speciality pharmacists, including pharmacist prescribers, pharmacy assistants and technicians.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will participate in our structured rotational development programme and gain comprehensive experience in all aspects of hospital pharmacy at this acute general hospital Trust. Opportunities exist to rotate through medicines information, aseptic dispensing and numerous clinical specialties. We have close links with local Universities and you will have an opportunity to undertake a Diploma in Clinical Pharmacy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join a team of clinical resident pharmacists who provide our extended clinical service to patients within the Dudley Group Foundation Trust. Residents are provided with all appropriate resources, including advisory support from our experienced senior pharmacists. On site accommodation is provided during the week on-call, if required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If successful you will benefit from working within a dynamic department fully embracing the Hospital Pharmacy Transformation Plan (HPTP). This is an exciting time for the Dudley Group pharmacy team as we have just rolled out electronic prescribing and medicines administration (ePMA) and have secured additional funding to further expand and embed advanced clinical services to deliver direct care to patients within the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Michelle Haddock - Principal Pharmacist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: michelle.haddock@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01384 244 213&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For an informal chat and further information please contact Michelle Haddock or Louise Crathorne, Principal Pharmacists, Clinical Services 01384 244213&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
